Postpartum Journal Entry: recovering from a C-section is no joke, especially having to take care of a toddler and newborn. I’ve cried and stressed a lot (my poor husband and mom). I’m still swollen in my feet, ankles, and belly. So much that I’ve been asked twice when my baby is due (awkward). But I wouldn’t have it any other way because having Emma with us completes our family of four!// Emma completa nuestra familia perfectamente 💕P.S. EJ has been enjoying a lot of one on one time with dad and is loving it. 
.
.
.
.
.
.
#postpartum #postpartumbody #familyoffour #babyblues #hisandhers #newborn #newbornbabygirl #compressionsocks

I can’t believe I’m a mom of two. This time around I’m enjoying the newborn stage a lot more. I’m not as stressed or anxious. EJ still has his moments but we are starting to figure out ways to help with his emotions, (sometimes I sit down and cry with him too). Emma is such a sweetheart, I can’t get enough of her. Here’s a postpartum hack, have your baby during the holidays. It’s easier to snap out of the baby blues listening to Christmas music and taking walks outside. // no puedo creer que soy mamá de dos. Está ves estoy disfrutando el momento un poco más. 
.
.
.
.
.
#postpartumjourney #journal #momoftwo #twoweekold #twoyearold #motherhood #4thtrimester #holidays
